face-image: img/portraits/wirth.jpg

= <span style="color: #000000;">**Wirth**</span> Government unstable..

Our current coalition lead by Chancellor <span style="color: #000000;">**Joseph Wirth**</span> has been set increasingly under pressure for its "Erfüllungspolitik" (policy of fulfillment regarding the Versailles Treaty obligations).

<span style="color: #000000;">**Wirth**</span> is attempting to negotiate with the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>, attempting to convince them to join government along with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, with our parties <span style="color: #c00000;">**left-wing**</span> deeply opposed to this, who sees it as a betrayal of the workers.

There are a few options...
  
- @compromise: Hold up the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> arrangement.
- @allow_dvp_into_wirth: Agree to working together with the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>.
- @no_options_for_wirth: There is nothing we can do.

@compromise
subtitle: We do not have enough votes.
view-if: uspd_joined >= 1
choose-if: reformist_strength >= 45 and uspd_concession >= 5 and wirth_concession >= 2
on-arrival: z_relation -= 5; ddp_relation -= 3; center_dissent -= 3

We can sustain a <span style="color: #000000;">**We**</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">**im**</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">**ar**</span> majority as long as we find a compromise among our parties.

@allow_dvp_into_wirth
subtitle: <span style="color: #000000;">**Wirth**</span> tries to form a Grand Coalition
unavailable-subtitle: Our party is opposed to this.
choose-if: dvp_relation >= 50 and reformist_strength >= (left_strength + labor_strength) and early_dvp_cooperation >= 3
on-arrival: kpd_relation -= 20; uspd_relation -= 15; workers_spd -= 3; unemployed_spd -= 3; in_grand_coalition = 1; in_weimar_coalition = 0; dvp_in_government = 1; foreign_minister_party = "DVP"; foreign_minister = "Stresemann"; left_dissent += 10; center_dissent += 2; labor_dissent += 2

The <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> has already given up the Foreign ministry. We have to give them one of our ministries now.

- @drop_economic: Drop the Economic ministry
- @drop_justice: Drop the Justice ministry
- @drop_interior: Drop the Interior ministry

@drop_economic
on-arrival: economic_minister_party = "DVP"; economic_minister = "Becker"

The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> joins our government. This is something new entirely...

@drop_justice
on-arrival: justice_minister_party = "DVP"; justice_minister = "Heinze"

The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> joins our government. This is something new entirely...

@drop_interior
unavailable-subtitle: This won't happen.
choose-if: dvp_relation >= 1919
go-to: allow_dvp_into_wirth

You have pulled a cheat to press a button that literally does nothing. Cheater.

- @drop_economic: Drop the Economic ministry
- @drop_justice: Drop the Justice ministry

@no_options_for_wirth
subtitle: We can't work with the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>, we can't sustain our current coalition, there is no other way out.
on-arrival: wirth_2_failed = 1; old_middle_spd -= 1; new_middle_z -= 2; workers_kpd += 1; rural_dnvp += 2; old_middle_dnvp += 2; new_middle_dvp += 1

<span style="color: #000000;">Wirth</span> needs to resign. <span style="color: #c00000;">**Ebert**</span> will choose a new chancelor...

